# Finance Dashboard — project context

Behavioral rules: [golden-rule.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/golden-rule.mdc). Below is repository-specific context only.

## Layout

- `backend/` — Express + Prisma + SQLite (`prisma/schema.prisma`, `src/app.ts`, `src/fx.ts`)
- `frontend/` — Vite + React + TypeScript (`src/components/`, `src/api/`, `src/state/`)
- Repository root: `npm run dev`, `npm run build`

## Running locally

- Backend: `http://localhost:4000` (`cd backend && npm run dev`)
- Frontend: `http://localhost:5173` (`cd frontend && npm run dev`)
- Both: `npm run dev` from the repository root

## Database

After changing models in `backend/prisma/schema.prisma`:

```bash
cd backend && npx prisma migrate dev --name <migration_description>
```

## Code changes

- Minimal diff; no refactors outside the task scope (see golden-rule).
- New endpoints should match existing handlers in `app.ts`.
- New views/components under `frontend/src/components/`; API client code under `frontend/src/api/`.
